#!/bin/bash
set -euo pipefail

chmod 0755 /usr/lib/remote-sudo-touch/remote-sudo-touch || true
chmod 0644 /etc/remote-sudo-touch/config.env || true

cat <<'MSG'
remote-sudo-touch installed.

PAM integration is intentionally not auto-enabled.
Review this snippet and add it to /etc/pam.d/sudo if desired:

  auth sufficient pam_exec.so quiet /usr/lib/remote-sudo-touch/remote-sudo-touch

Snippet file:
  /usr/share/remote-sudo-touch/pam/sudo-snippet

Before enabling PAM, confirm your reverse SSH tunnel is working and that
localhost:9876 on Ubuntu reaches the Mac-side RemoteSudoTouch agent.
MSG
